data.name: UnknownServerError
data.value: The server experienced an unexpected error when processing the request.

data.name: OffsetOutOfRange
data.value: The requested offset is not within the range of offsets maintained by the server.

data.name: CorruptMessage
data.value: This message has failed its CRC checksum, exceeds the valid size, has a null key for a compacted topic, or is otherwise corrupt.

data.name: UnknownTopicOrPartition
data.value: This server does not host this topic-partition.

data.name: InvalidFetchSize
data.value: The requested fetch size is invalid.

data.name: LeaderNotAvailable
data.value: There is no leader for this topic-partition as we are in the middle of a leadership election.

data.name: NotLeaderOrFollower
data.value: For requests intended only for the leader, this error indicates that the broker is not the current leader. For requests intended for any replica, this error indicates that the broker is not a replica of the topic partition.

data.name: RequestTimedOut
data.value: The request timed out.

data.name: BrokerNotAvailable
data.value: The broker is not available.

data.name: ReplicaNotAvailable
data.value: The replica is not available for the requested topic-partition. Produce/Fetch requests and other requests intended only for the leader or follower return NotLeaderOrFollower if the broker is not a replica of the topic-partition.

data.name: MessageTooLarge
data.value: The request included a message larger than the max message size the server will accept.

data.name: StaleControllerEpoch
data.value: The controller moved to another broker.

data.name: OffsetMetadataTooLarge
data.value: The metadata field of the offset request was too large.

data.name: NetworkException
data.value: The server disconnected before a response was received.

data.name: CoordinatorLoadInProgress
data.value: The coordinator is loading and hence can't process requests.

data.name: CoordinatorNotAvailable
data.value: The coordinator is not available.

data.name: NotCoordinator
data.value: This is not the correct coordinator.

data.name: InvalidTopicException
data.value: The request attempted to perform an operation on an invalid topic.

data.name: RecordListTooLarge
data.value: The request included message batch larger than the configured segment size on the server.

data.name: NotEnoughReplicas
data.value: Messages are rejected since there are fewer in-sync replicas than required.

data.name: NotEnoughReplicasAfterAppend
data.value: Messages are written to the log, but to fewer in-sync replicas than required.

data.name: InvalidRequiredAcks
data.value: Produce request specified an invalid value for required acks.

data.name: IllegalGeneration
data.value: Specified group generation id is not valid.

data.name: InconsistentGroupProtocol
data.value: The group member's supported protocols are incompatible with those of existing members or first group member tried to join with empty protocol type or empty protocol list.

data.name: InvalidGroupId
data.value: The configured groupId is invalid.

data.name: UnknownMemberId
data.value: The coordinator is not aware of this member.

data.name: InvalidSessionTimeout
data.value: The session timeout is not within the range allowed by the broker (as configured by group.min.session.timeout.ms and group.max.session.timeout.ms).

data.name: RebalanceInProgress
data.value: The group is rebalancing, so a rejoin is needed.

data.name: InvalidCommitOffsetSize
data.value: The committing offset data size is not valid.

data.name: TopicAuthorizationFailed
data.value: Topic authorization failed.

data.name: GroupAuthorizationFailed
data.value: Group authorization failed.

data.name: ClusterAuthorizationFailed
data.value: Cluster authorization failed.

data.name: InvalidTimestamp
data.value: The timestamp of the message is out of acceptable range.

data.name: UnsupportedSaslMechanism
data.value: The broker does not support the requested SASL mechanism.

data.name: IllegalSaslState
data.value: Request is not valid given the current SASL state.

data.name: UnsupportedVersion
data.value: The version of API is not supported.

data.name: TopicAlreadyExists
data.value: Topic with this name already exists.

data.name: InvalidPartitions
data.value: Number of partitions is below 1.

data.name: InvalidReplicationFactor
data.value: Replication factor is below 1 or larger than the number of available brokers.

data.name: InvalidReplicaAssignment
data.value: Replica assignment is invalid.

data.name: InvalidConfig
data.value: Configuration is invalid.

data.name: NotController
data.value: This is not the correct controller for this cluster.

data.name: InvalidRequest
data.value: This most likely occurs because of a request being malformed by the client library or the message was sent to an incompatible broker. See the broker logs for more details.

data.name: UnsupportedForMessageFormat
data.value: The message format version on the broker does not support the request.

data.name: PolicyViolation
data.value: Request parameters do not satisfy the configured policy.

data.name: OutOfOrderSequenceNumber
data.value: The broker received an out of order sequence number.

data.name: DuplicateSequenceNumber
data.value: The broker received a duplicate sequence number.

data.name: InvalidProducerEpoch
data.value: Producer attempted to produce with an old epoch.

data.name: InvalidTxnState
data.value: The producer attempted a transactional operation in an invalid state.

data.name: InvalidProducerIdMapping
data.value: The producer attempted to use a producer id which is not currently assigned to its transactional id.

data.name: InvalidTransactionTimeout
data.value: The transaction timeout is larger than the maximum value allowed by the broker (as configured by transaction.max.timeout.ms).

data.name: ConcurrentTransactions
data.value: The producer attempted to update a transaction while another concurrent operation on the same transaction was ongoing.

data.name: TransactionCoordinatorFenced
data.value: Indicates that the transaction coordinator sending a WriteTxnMarker is no longer the current coordinator for a given producer.

data.name: TransactionalIdAuthorizationFailed
data.value: Transactional Id authorization failed.

data.name: SecurityDisabled
data.value: Security features are disabled.

data.name: OperationNotAttempted
data.value: The broker did not attempt to execute this operation. This may happen for batched RPCs where some operations in the batch failed, causing the broker to respond without trying the rest.

data.name: KafkaStorageError
data.value: Disk error when trying to access log file on the disk.

data.name: LogDirNotFound
data.value: The user-specified log directory is not found in the broker config.

data.name: SaslAuthenticationFailed
data.value: SASL Authentication failed.

data.name: UnknownProducerId
data.value: This exception is raised by the broker if it could not locate the producer metadata associated with the producerId in question. This could happen if, for instance, the producer's records were deleted because their retention time had elapsed. Once the last records of the producerId are removed, the producer's metadata is removed from the broker, and future appends by the producer will return thisexception.

data.name: ReassignmentInProgress
data.value: A partition reassignment is in progress.

data.name: DelegationTokenAuthDisabled
data.value: Delegation Token feature is not enabled.

data.name: DelegationTokenNotFound
data.value: Delegation Token is not found on server.

data.name: DelegationTokenOwnerMismatch
data.value: Specified Principal is not valid Owner/Renewer.

data.name: DelegationTokenRequestNotAllowed
data.value: Delegation Token requests are not allowed on PLAINTEXT/1-way SSL channels and on delegation token authenticated channels.

data.name: DelegationTokenAuthorizationFailed
data.value: Delegation Token authorization failed.

data.name: DelegationTokenExpired
data.value: Delegation Token is expired.

data.name: InvalidPrincipalType
data.value: Supplied principalType is not supported.

data.name: NonEmptyGroup
data.value: The group is not empty.

data.name: GroupIdNotFound
data.value: The group id does not exist.

data.name: FetchSessionIdNotFound
data.value: The fetch session ID was not found.

data.name: InvalidFetchSessionEpoch
data.value: The fetch session epoch is invalid.

data.name: ListenerNotFound
data.value: There is no listener on the leader broker that matches the listener on which metadata request was processed.

data.name: TopicDeletionDisabled
data.value: Topic deletion is disabled.

data.name: FencedLeaderEpoch
data.value: The leader epoch in the request is older than the epoch on the broker.

data.name: UnknownLeaderEpoch
data.value: The leader epoch in the request is newer than the epoch on the broker.

data.name: UnsupportedCompressionType
data.value: The requesting client does not support the compression type of given partition.

data.name: StaleBrokerEpoch
data.value: Broker epoch has changed.

data.name: OffsetNotAvailable
data.value: The leader high watermark has not caught up from a recent leader election so the offsets cannot be guaranteed to be monotonically increasing.

data.name: MemberIdRequired
data.value: The group member needs to have a valid member id before actually entering a consumer group.

data.name: PreferredLeaderNotAvailable
data.value: The preferred leader was not available.

data.name: GroupMaxSizeReached
data.value: The consumer group has reached its max size.

data.name: FencedInstanceId
data.value: The broker rejected this static consumer since another consumer with the same group.instance.id has registered with a different member.id.

data.name: EligibleLeadersNotAvailable
data.value: Eligible topic partition leaders are not available.

data.name: ElectionNotNeeded
data.value: Leader election not needed for topic partition.

data.name: NoReassignmentInProgress
data.value: No partition reassignment is in progress.

data.name: GroupSubscribedToTopic
data.value: Deleting offsets of a topic is forbidden while the consumer group is actively subscribed to it.

data.name: InvalidRecord
data.value: This record has failed the validation on broker and hence will be rejected.

data.name: UnstableOffsetCommit
data.value: There are unstable offsets that need to be cleared.

data.name: ThrottlingQuotaExceeded
data.value: The throttling quota has been exceeded.

data.name: ProducerFenced
data.value: There is a newer producer with the same transactionalId which fences the current one.

data.name: ResourceNotFound
data.value: A request illegally referred to a resource that does not exist.

data.name: DuplicateResource
data.value: A request illegally referred to the same resource twice.

data.name: UnacceptableCredential
data.value: Requested credential would not meet criteria for acceptability.

data.name: InconsistentVoterSet
data.value: Indicates that the either the sender or recipient of a voter-only request is not one of the expected voters

data.name: InvalidUpdateVersion
data.value: The given update version was invalid.

data.name: FeatureUpdateFailed
data.value: Unable to update finalized features due to an unexpected server error.

data.name: PrincipalDeserializationFailure
data.value: Request principal deserialization failed during forwarding. This indicates an internal error on the broker cluster security setup.

data.name: SnapshotNotFound
data.value: Requested snapshot was not found

data.name: PositionOutOfRange
data.value: Requested position is not greater than or equal to zero, and less than the size of the snapshot.

data.name: UnknownTopicId
data.value: This server does not host this topic ID.

data.name: DuplicateBrokerRegistration
data.value: This broker ID is already in use.

data.name: BrokerIdNotRegistered
data.value: The given broker ID was not registered.

data.name: InconsistentTopicId
data.value: The log's topic ID did not match the topic ID in the request

data.name: InconsistentClusterId
data.value: The clusterId in the request does not match that found on the server

data.name: TransactionalIdNotFound
data.value: The transactionalId could not be found

data.name: FetchSessionTopicIdError
data.value: The fetch session encountered inconsistent topic ID usage

data.name: IneligibleReplica
data.value: The new ISR contains at least one ineligible replica.

data.name: NewLeaderElected
data.value: The AlterPartition request successfully updated the partition state but the leader has changed.
